properties.headline: Special Weather Statement issued February 5 at 11:09AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
Multiple periods of rainfall since the first of January has
increased soil moisture to high levels across western Washington.
Rainfall amounts of up to 2 inches over the last 24 hours with locally
higher amounts of 3 to 4 inches for portions of the Cascades.
Additional rainfall through Friday with up 3 or more inches in the
lowlands and foothills. This amount of rain will put extra pressure
on soil instability, leading to an increased threat of landslides
being triggered through the period and immediately after.

Areas above 5000 feet in elevation will see mostly snow and not be
affected.

A landslide has already been reported in Clallam County in western
Washington near Beaver. More landslides are possible.

For more information about current conditions, visit
www.weather.gov/seattle, select Hydrology, and then scroll down
for the links to the landslide information pages.

For more information on landslides, visit the website for the
Washington State Department of Natural Resources landslide
geologic hazards at: http://bit.ly/2mtA3wn

NWSheadline: HEAVY RAINFALL ON THROUGH FRIDAY WILL LEAD TO AN INCREASED THREAT OF LANDSLIDES IN WESTERN WASHINGTON
